4212OverflowResult llvm::computeOverflowForUnsignedAdd(
4213 const Value *LHS, const Value *RHS, const DataLayout &DL,
4214 AssumptionCache *AC, const Instruction *CxtI, const DominatorTree *DT,
4215 bool UseInstrInfo) {
4216 ConstantRange LHSRange = computeConstantRangeIncludingKnownBits(
4217 LHS, /*ForSigned=*/false, DL, /*Depth=*/0, AC, CxtI, DT,
4218 nullptr, UseInstrInfo);
4219 ConstantRange RHSRange = computeConstantRangeIncludingKnownBits(
4220 RHS, /*ForSigned=*/false, DL, /*Depth=*/0, AC, CxtI, DT,
4221 nullptr, UseInstrInfo);
4222 return mapOverflowResult(LHSRange.unsignedAddMayOverflow(RHSRange));
4223}
4224
4225static OverflowResult computeOverflowForSignedAdd(const Value *LHS,
4226 const Value *RHS,
4227 const AddOperator *Add,
4228 const DataLayout &DL,
4229 AssumptionCache *AC,
4230 const Instruction *CxtI,
4231 const DominatorTree *DT) {
4232 if (Add && Add->hasNoSignedWrap()) {
4233 return OverflowResult::NeverOverflows;
4234 }
4235
4236 // If LHS and RHS each have at least two sign bits, the addition will look
4237 // like
4238 //
4239 // XX..... +
4240 // YY.....
4241 //
4242 // If the carry into the most significant position is 0, X and Y can't both
4243 // be 1 and therefore the carry out of the addition is also 0.
4244 //
4245 // If the carry into the most significant position is 1, X and Y can't both
4246 // be 0 and therefore the carry out of the addition is also 1.
4247 //
4248 // Since the carry into the most significant position is always equal to
4249 // the carry out of the addition, there is no signed overflow.
4250 if (ComputeNumSignBits(LHS, DL, 0, AC, CxtI, DT) > 1 &&
4251 ComputeNumSignBits(RHS, DL, 0, AC, CxtI, DT) > 1)
4252 return OverflowResult::NeverOverflows;
4253
4254 ConstantRange LHSRange = computeConstantRangeIncludingKnownBits(
4255 LHS, /*ForSigned=*/true, DL, /*Depth=*/0, AC, CxtI, DT);
4256 ConstantRange RHSRange = computeConstantRangeIncludingKnownBits(
4257 RHS, /*ForSigned=*/true, DL, /*Depth=*/0, AC, CxtI, DT);
4258 OverflowResult OR =
4259 mapOverflowResult(LHSRange.signedAddMayOverflow(RHSRange));
4260 if (OR != OverflowResult::MayOverflow)
4261 return OR;
4262
4263 // The remaining code needs Add to be available. Early returns if not so.
4264 if (!Add)
4265 return OverflowResult::MayOverflow;
4266
4267 // If the sign of Add is the same as at least one of the operands, this add
4268 // CANNOT overflow. If this can be determined from the known bits of the
4269 // operands the above signedAddMayOverflow() check will have already done so.
4270 // The only other way to improve on the known bits is from an assumption, so
4271 // call computeKnownBitsFromAssume() directly.
4272 bool LHSOrRHSKnownNonNegative =
4273 (LHSRange.isAllNonNegative() || RHSRange.isAllNonNegative());
4274 bool LHSOrRHSKnownNegative =
4275 (LHSRange.isAllNegative() || RHSRange.isAllNegative());
4276 if (LHSOrRHSKnownNonNegative || LHSOrRHSKnownNegative) {
4277 KnownBits AddKnown(LHSRange.getBitWidth());
4278 computeKnownBitsFromAssume(
4279 Add, AddKnown, /*Depth=*/0, Query(DL, AC, CxtI, DT, true));
4280 if ((AddKnown.isNonNegative() && LHSOrRHSKnownNonNegative) ||
4281 (AddKnown.isNegative() && LHSOrRHSKnownNegative))
4282 return OverflowResult::NeverOverflows;
4283 }
4284
4285 return OverflowResult::MayOverflow;
4286}

4288OverflowResult llvm::computeOverflowForUnsignedSub(const Value *LHS,
4289 const Value *RHS,
4290 const DataLayout &DL,
4291 AssumptionCache *AC,
4292 const Instruction *CxtI,
4293 const DominatorTree *DT) {
4294 ConstantRange LHSRange = computeConstantRangeIncludingKnownBits(
4295 LHS, /*ForSigned=*/false, DL, /*Depth=*/0, AC, CxtI, DT);
4296 ConstantRange RHSRange = computeConstantRangeIncludingKnownBits(
4297 RHS, /*ForSigned=*/false, DL, /*Depth=*/0, AC, CxtI, DT);
4298 return mapOverflowResult(LHSRange.unsignedSubMayOverflow(RHSRange));
4299}

4301OverflowResult llvm::computeOverflowForSignedSub(const Value *LHS,
4302 const Value *RHS,
4303 const DataLayout &DL,
4304 AssumptionCache *AC,
4305 const Instruction *CxtI,
4306 const DominatorTree *DT) {
4307 // If LHS and RHS each have at least two sign bits, the subtraction

4318}

4320bool llvm::isOverflowIntrinsicNoWrap(const WithOverflowInst *WO,
4321 const DominatorTree &DT) {
4322 SmallVector<const BranchInst *, 2> GuardingBranches;
4323 SmallVector<const ExtractValueInst *, 2> Results;
4324
4325 for (const User *U : WO->users()) {
4326 if (const auto *EVI = dyn_cast<ExtractValueInst>(U)) {
4327 assert(EVI->getNumIndices() == 1 && "Obvious from CI's type");
4328
4329 if (EVI->getIndices()[0] == 0)
4330 Results.push_back(EVI);
4331 else {
4332 assert(EVI->getIndices()[0] == 1 && "Obvious from CI's type");
4333
4334 for (const auto *U : EVI->users())
4335 if (const auto *B = dyn_cast<BranchInst>(U)) {
4336 assert(B->isConditional() && "How else is it using an i1?");
4337 GuardingBranches.push_back(B);
4338 }
4339 }
4340 } else {
4341 // We are using the aggregate directly in a way we don't want to analyze
4342 // here (storing it to a global, say).
4343 return false;
4344 }
4345 }
4346
4347 auto AllUsesGuardedByBranch = [&](const BranchInst *BI) {
4348 BasicBlockEdge NoWrapEdge(BI->getParent(), BI->getSuccessor(1));
4349 if (!NoWrapEdge.isSingleEdge())
4350 return false;
4351
4352 // Check if all users of the add are provably no-wrap.
4353 for (const auto *Result : Results) {
4354 // If the extractvalue itself is not executed on overflow, the we don't
4355 // need to check each use separately, since domination is transitive.
4356 if (DT.dominates(NoWrapEdge, Result->getParent()))
4357 continue;
4358
4359 for (auto &RU : Result->uses())
4360 if (!DT.dominates(NoWrapEdge, RU))
4361 return false;
4362 }
4363
4364 return true;
4365 };
4366
4367 return llvm::any_of(GuardingBranches, AllUsesGuardedByBranch);
4368}

4388
4389bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(const Instruction *I) {
4390 // A memory operation returns normally if it isn't volatile. A volatile
4391 // operation is allowed to trap.
4392 //
4393 // An atomic operation isn't guaranteed to return in a reasonable amount of
4394 // time because it's possible for another thread to interfere with it for an
4395 // arbitrary length of time, but programs aren't allowed to rely on that.
4396 if (const LoadInst *LI = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(I))
4397 return !LI->isVolatile();
4398 if (const StoreInst *SI = dyn_cast<StoreInst>(I))
4399 return !SI->isVolatile();
4400 if (const AtomicCmpXchgInst *CXI = dyn_cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I))
4401 return !CXI->isVolatile();
4402 if (const AtomicRMWInst *RMWI = dyn_cast<AtomicRMWInst>(I))
4403 return !RMWI->isVolatile();
4404 if (const MemIntrinsic *MII = dyn_cast<MemIntrinsic>(I))
4405 return !MII->isVolatile();
4406
4407 // If there is no successor, then execution can't transfer to it.
4408 if (const auto *CRI = dyn_cast<CleanupReturnInst>(I))
4409 return !CRI->unwindsToCaller();
4410 if (const auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast<CatchSwitchInst>(I))
4411 return !CatchSwitch->unwindsToCaller();
4412 if (isa<ResumeInst>(I))
4413 return false;
4414 if (isa<ReturnInst>(I))
4415 return false;
4416 if (isa<UnreachableInst>(I))
4417 return false;
4418
4419 // Calls can throw, or contain an infinite loop, or kill the process.
4420 if (auto CS = ImmutableCallSite(I)) {
4421 // Call sites that throw have implicit non-local control flow.
4422 if (!CS.doesNotThrow())
4423 return false;
4424
4425 // Non-throwing call sites can loop infinitely, call exit/pthread_exit
4426 // etc. and thus not return. However, LLVM already assumes that
4427 //
4428 // - Thread exiting actions are modeled as writes to memory invisible to
4429 // the program.
4430 //
4431 // - Loops that don't have side effects (side effects are volatile/atomic
4432 // stores and IO) always terminate (see http://llvm.org/PR965).
4433 // Furthermore IO itself is also modeled as writes to memory invisible to
4434 // the program.
4435 //
4436 // We rely on those assumptions here, and use the memory effects of the call
4437 // target as a proxy for checking that it always returns.
4438
4439 // FIXME: This isn't aggressive enough; a call which only writes to a global
4440 // is guaranteed to return.
4441 return CS.onlyReadsMemory() || CS.onlyAccessesArgMemory() ||
4442 match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::assume>()) ||
4443 match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::sideeffect>()) ||
4444 match(I, m_Intrinsic<Intrinsic::experimental_widenable_condition>());
4445 }
4446
4447 // Other instructions return normally.
4448 return true;
4449}
4450
4451bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(const BasicBlock *BB) {
4452 // TODO: This is slightly conservative for invoke instruction since exiting
4453 // via an exception *is* normal control for them.
4454 for (auto I = BB->begin(), E = BB->end(); I != E; ++I)
4455 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&*I))
4456 return false;
4457 return true;
4458}
4459
4460bool llvm::isGuaranteedToExecuteForEveryIteration(const Instruction *I,
4461 const Loop *L) {
4462 // The loop header is guaranteed to be executed for every iteration.
4463 //
4464 // FIXME: Relax this constraint to cover all basic blocks that are
4465 // guaranteed to be executed at every iteration.
4466 if (I->getParent() != L->getHeader()) return false;
4467
4468 for (const Instruction &LI : *L->getHeader()) {
4469 if (&LI == I) return true;
4470 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&LI)) return false;
4471 }
4472 llvm_unreachable("Instruction not contained in its own parent basic block.");
4473}

4475bool llvm::propagatesFullPoison(const Instruction *I) {
4476 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
4477 case Instruction::Add:
4478 case Instruction::Sub:
4479 case Instruction::Xor:
4480 case Instruction::Trunc:
4481 case Instruction::BitCast:
4482 case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast:
4483 case Instruction::Mul:
4484 case Instruction::Shl:
4485 case Instruction::GetElementPtr:
4486 // These operations all propagate poison unconditionally. Note that poison
4487 // is not any particular value, so xor or subtraction of poison with
4488 // itself still yields poison, not zero.
4489 return true;
4490
4491 case Instruction::AShr:
4492 case Instruction::SExt:
4493 // For these operations, one bit of the input is replicated across
4494 // multiple output bits. A replicated poison bit is still poison.
4495 return true;
4496
4497 case Instruction::ICmp:
4498 // Comparing poison with any value yields poison. This is why, for
4499 // instance, x s< (x +nsw 1) can be folded to true.
4500 return true;
4501
4502 default:
4503 return false;
4504 }
4505}
4506
4507const Value *llvm::getGuaranteedNonFullPoisonOp(const Instruction *I) {
4508 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
4509 case Instruction::Store:
4510 return cast<StoreInst>(I)->getPointerOperand();
4511
4512 case Instruction::Load:
4513 return cast<LoadInst>(I)->getPointerOperand();
4514
4515 case Instruction::AtomicCmpXchg:
4516 return cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I)->getPointerOperand();
4517
4518 case Instruction::AtomicRMW:
4519 return cast<AtomicRMWInst>(I)->getPointerOperand();
4520
4521 case Instruction::UDiv:
4522 case Instruction::SDiv:
4523 case Instruction::URem:
4524 case Instruction::SRem:
4525 return I->getOperand(1);
4526
4527 default:
4528 return nullptr;
4529 }
4530}
4531
4532bool llvm::mustTriggerUB(const Instruction *I,
4533 const SmallSet<const Value *, 16>& KnownPoison) {
4534 auto *NotPoison = getGuaranteedNonFullPoisonOp(I);
4535 return (NotPoison && KnownPoison.count(NotPoison));
4536}

4538
4539bool llvm::programUndefinedIfFullPoison(const Instruction *PoisonI) {
4540 // We currently only look for uses of poison values within the same basic
4541 // block, as that makes it easier to guarantee that the uses will be
4542 // executed given that PoisonI is executed.
4543 //
4544 // FIXME: Expand this to consider uses beyond the same basic block. To do
4545 // this, look out for the distinction between post-dominance and strong
4546 // post-dominance.
4547 const BasicBlock *BB = PoisonI->getParent();
4548
4549 // Set of instructions that we have proved will yield poison if PoisonI
4550 // does.
4551 SmallSet<const Value *, 16> YieldsPoison;
4552 SmallSet<const BasicBlock *, 4> Visited;
4553 YieldsPoison.insert(PoisonI);
4554 Visited.insert(PoisonI->getParent());
4555
4556 BasicBlock::const_iterator Begin = PoisonI->getIterator(), End = BB->end();
4557
4558 unsigned Iter = 0;
4559 while (Iter++ < MaxDepth) {
4560 for (auto &I : make_range(Begin, End)) {
4561 if (&I != PoisonI) {
4562 if (mustTriggerUB(&I, YieldsPoison))
4563 return true;
4564 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
4565 return false;
4566 }
4567
4568 // Mark poison that propagates from I through uses of I.
4569 if (YieldsPoison.count(&I)) {
4570 for (const User *User : I.users()) {
4571 const Instruction *UserI = cast<Instruction>(User);
4572 if (propagatesFullPoison(UserI))
4573 YieldsPoison.insert(User);
4574 }
4575 }
4576 }
4577
4578 if (auto *NextBB = BB->getSingleSuccessor()) {
4579 if (Visited.insert(NextBB).second) {
4580 BB = NextBB;
4581 Begin = BB->getFirstNonPHI()->getIterator();
4582 End = BB->end();
4583 continue;
4584 }
4585 }
4586
4587 break;
4588 }
4589 return false;
4590}

4592static bool isKnownNonNaN(const Value *V, FastMathFlags FMF) {
4593 if (FMF.noNaNs())
4594 return true;
4595
4596 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(V))
4597 return !C->isNaN();
4598
4599 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantDataVector>(V)) {
4600 if (!C->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy())
4601 return false;
4602 for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumElements(); I < E; ++I) {
4603 if (C->getElementAsAPFloat(I).isNaN())
4604 return false;
4605 }
4606 return true;
4607 }
4608
4609 return false;
4610}

4629/// Match clamp pattern for float types without care about NaNs or signed zeros.
4630/// Given non-min/max outer cmp/select from the clamp pattern this
4631/// function recognizes if it can be substitued by a "canonical" min/max
4632/// pattern.
4633static SelectPatternResult matchFastFloatClamp(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
4634 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
4635 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
4636 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS) {
4637 // Try to match
4638 // X < C1 ? C1 : Min(X, C2) --> Max(C1, Min(X, C2))
4639 // X > C1 ? C1 : Max(X, C2) --> Min(C1, Max(X, C2))
4640 // and return description of the outer Max/Min.
4641
4642 // First, check if select has inverse order:
4643 if (CmpRHS == FalseVal) {
4644 std::swap(TrueVal, FalseVal);
4645 Pred = CmpInst::getInversePredicate(Pred);
4646 }
4647
4648 // Assume success now. If there's no match, callers should not use these anyway.
4649 LHS = TrueVal;
4650 RHS = FalseVal;
4651
4652 const APFloat *FC1;
4653 if (CmpRHS != TrueVal || !match(CmpRHS, m_APFloat(FC1)) || !FC1->isFinite())
4654 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4655
4656 const APFloat *FC2;
4657 switch (Pred) {
4658 case CmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
4659 case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
4660 case CmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
4661 case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
4662 if (match(FalseVal,
4663 m_CombineOr(m_OrdFMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)),
4664 m_UnordFMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)))) &&
4665 FC1->compare(*FC2) == APFloat::cmpResult::cmpLessThan)
4666 return {SPF_FMAXNUM, SPNB_RETURNS_ANY, false};
4667 break;
4668 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
4669 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
4670 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
4671 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
4672 if (match(FalseVal,
4673 m_CombineOr(m_OrdFMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)),
4674 m_UnordFMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)))) &&
4675 FC1->compare(*FC2) == APFloat::cmpResult::cmpGreaterThan)
4676 return {SPF_FMINNUM, SPNB_RETURNS_ANY, false};
4677 break;
4678 default:
4679 break;
4680 }
4681
4682 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4683}
4684
4685/// Recognize variations of:
4686/// CLAMP(v,l,h) ==> ((v) < (l) ? (l) : ((v) > (h) ? (h) : (v)))
4687static SelectPatternResult matchClamp(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
4688 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
4689 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal) {
4690 // Swap the select operands and predicate to match the patterns below.
4691 if (CmpRHS != TrueVal) {
4692 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
4693 std::swap(TrueVal, FalseVal);
4694 }
4695 const APInt *C1;
4696 if (CmpRHS == TrueVal && match(CmpRHS, m_APInt(C1))) {
4697 const APInt *C2;
4698 // (X <s C1) ? C1 : SMIN(X, C2) ==> SMAX(SMIN(X, C2), C1)
4699 if (match(FalseVal, m_SMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
4700 C1->slt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
4701 return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
4702
4703 // (X >s C1) ? C1 : SMAX(X, C2) ==> SMIN(SMAX(X, C2), C1)
4704 if (match(FalseVal, m_SMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
4705 C1->sgt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
4706 return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
4707
4708 // (X <u C1) ? C1 : UMIN(X, C2) ==> UMAX(UMIN(X, C2), C1)
4709 if (match(FalseVal, m_UMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
4710 C1->ult(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
4711 return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
4712
4713 // (X >u C1) ? C1 : UMAX(X, C2) ==> UMIN(UMAX(X, C2), C1)
4714 if (match(FalseVal, m_UMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
4715 C1->ugt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
4716 return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
4717 }
4718 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4719}
4720
4721/// Recognize variations of:
4722/// a < c ? min(a,b) : min(b,c) ==> min(min(a,b),min(b,c))
4723static SelectPatternResult matchMinMaxOfMinMax(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
4724 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
4725 Value *TVal, Value *FVal,
4726 unsigned Depth) {
4727 // TODO: Allow FP min/max with nnan/nsz.
4728 assert(CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred) && "Expected integer comparison");
4729
4730 Value *A, *B;
4731 SelectPatternResult L = matchSelectPattern(TVal, A, B, nullptr, Depth + 1);
4732 if (!SelectPatternResult::isMinOrMax(L.Flavor))
4733 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4734
4735 Value *C, *D;
4736 SelectPatternResult R = matchSelectPattern(FVal, C, D, nullptr, Depth + 1);
4737 if (L.Flavor != R.Flavor)
4738 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4739
4740 // We have something like: x Pred y ? min(a, b) : min(c, d).
4741 // Try to match the compare to the min/max operations of the select operands.
4742 // First, make sure we have the right compare predicate.
4743 switch (L.Flavor) {
4744 case SPF_SMIN:
4745 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE) {
4746 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
4747 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
4748 }
4749 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
4750 break;
4751 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4752 case SPF_SMAX:
4753 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE) {
4754 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
4755 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
4756 }
4757 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE)
4758 break;
4759 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4760 case SPF_UMIN:
4761 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE) {
4762 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
4763 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
4764 }
4765 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
4766 break;
4767 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4768 case SPF_UMAX:
4769 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE) {
4770 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
4771 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
4772 }
4773 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
4774 break;
4775 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4776 default:
4777 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4778 }
4779
4780 // If there is a common operand in the already matched min/max and the other
4781 // min/max operands match the compare operands (either directly or inverted),
4782 // then this is min/max of the same flavor.
4783
4784 // a pred c ? m(a, b) : m(c, b) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, b))
4785 // ~c pred ~a ? m(a, b) : m(c, b) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, b))
4786 if (D == B) {
4787 if ((CmpLHS == A && CmpRHS == C) || (match(C, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
4788 match(A, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
4789 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
4790 }
4791 // a pred d ? m(a, b) : m(b, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(b, d))
4792 // ~d pred ~a ? m(a, b) : m(b, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(b, d))
4793 if (C == B) {
4794 if ((CmpLHS == A && CmpRHS == D) || (match(D, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
4795 match(A, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
4796 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
4797 }
4798 // b pred c ? m(a, b) : m(c, a) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, a))
4799 // ~c pred ~b ? m(a, b) : m(c, a) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, a))
4800 if (D == A) {
4801 if ((CmpLHS == B && CmpRHS == C) || (match(C, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
4802 match(B, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
4803 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
4804 }
4805 // b pred d ? m(a, b) : m(a, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(a, d))
4806 // ~d pred ~b ? m(a, b) : m(a, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(a, d))
4807 if (C == A) {
4808 if ((CmpLHS == B && CmpRHS == D) || (match(D, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
4809 match(B, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
4810 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
4811 }
4812
4813 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4814}
4815
4816/// Match non-obvious integer minimum and maximum sequences.
4817static SelectPatternResult matchMinMax(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
4818 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
4819 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
4820 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
4821 unsigned Depth) {
4822 // Assume success. If there's no match, callers should not use these anyway.
4823 LHS = TrueVal;
4824 RHS = FalseVal;
4825
4826 SelectPatternResult SPR = matchClamp(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal);
4827 if (SPR.Flavor != SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_UNKNOWN)
4828 return SPR;
4829
4830 SPR = matchMinMaxOfMinMax(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, Depth);
4831 if (SPR.Flavor != SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_UNKNOWN)
4832 return SPR;
4833
4834 if (Pred != CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && Pred != CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
4835 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4836
4837 // Z = X -nsw Y
4838 // (X >s Y) ? 0 : Z ==> (Z >s 0) ? 0 : Z ==> SMIN(Z, 0)
4839 // (X <s Y) ? 0 : Z ==> (Z <s 0) ? 0 : Z ==> SMAX(Z, 0)
4840 if (match(TrueVal, m_Zero()) &&
4841 match(FalseVal, m_NSWSub(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_Specific(CmpRHS))))
4842 return {Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT ? SPF_SMIN : SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
4843
4844 // Z = X -nsw Y
4845 // (X >s Y) ? Z : 0 ==> (Z >s 0) ? Z : 0 ==> SMAX(Z, 0)
4846 // (X <s Y) ? Z : 0 ==> (Z <s 0) ? Z : 0 ==> SMIN(Z, 0)
4847 if (match(FalseVal, m_Zero()) &&
4848 match(TrueVal, m_NSWSub(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_Specific(CmpRHS))))
4849 return {Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT ? SPF_SMAX : SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
4850
4851 const APInt *C1;
4852 if (!match(CmpRHS, m_APInt(C1)))
4853 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4854
4855 // An unsigned min/max can be written with a signed compare.
4856 const APInt *C2;
4857 if ((CmpLHS == TrueVal && match(FalseVal, m_APInt(C2))) ||
4858 (CmpLHS == FalseVal && match(TrueVal, m_APInt(C2)))) {
4859 // Is the sign bit set?
4860 // (X <s 0) ? X : MAXVAL ==> (X >u MAXVAL) ? X : MAXVAL ==> UMAX
4861 // (X <s 0) ? MAXVAL : X ==> (X >u MAXVAL) ? MAXVAL : X ==> UMIN
4862 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT && C1->isNullValue() &&
4863 C2->isMaxSignedValue())
4864 return {CmpLHS == TrueVal ? SPF_UMAX : SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
4865
4866 // Is the sign bit clear?
4867 // (X >s -1) ? MINVAL : X ==> (X <u MINVAL) ? MINVAL : X ==> UMAX
4868 // (X >s -1) ? X : MINVAL ==> (X <u MINVAL) ? X : MINVAL ==> UMIN
4869 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && C1->isAllOnesValue() &&
4870 C2->isMinSignedValue())
4871 return {CmpLHS == FalseVal ? SPF_UMAX : SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
4872 }
4873
4874 // Look through 'not' ops to find disguised signed min/max.
4875 // (X >s C) ? ~X : ~C ==> (~X <s ~C) ? ~X : ~C ==> SMIN(~X, ~C)
4876 // (X <s C) ? ~X : ~C ==> (~X >s ~C) ? ~X : ~C ==> SMAX(~X, ~C)
4877 if (match(TrueVal, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
4878 match(FalseVal, m_APInt(C2)) && ~(*C1) == *C2)
4879 return {Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT ? SPF_SMIN : SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
4880
4881 // (X >s C) ? ~C : ~X ==> (~X <s ~C) ? ~C : ~X ==> SMAX(~C, ~X)
4882 // (X <s C) ? ~C : ~X ==> (~X >s ~C) ? ~C : ~X ==> SMIN(~C, ~X)
4883 if (match(FalseVal, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
4884 match(TrueVal, m_APInt(C2)) && ~(*C1) == *C2)
4885 return {Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT ? SPF_SMAX : SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
4886
4887 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4888}
4889
4890bool llvm::isKnownNegation(const Value *X, const Value *Y, bool NeedNSW) {
4891 assert(X && Y && "Invalid operand");
4892
4893 // X = sub (0, Y) || X = sub nsw (0, Y)
4894 if ((!NeedNSW && match(X, m_Sub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(Y)))) ||
4895 (NeedNSW && match(X, m_NSWSub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(Y)))))
4896 return true;
4897
4898 // Y = sub (0, X) || Y = sub nsw (0, X)
4899 if ((!NeedNSW && match(Y, m_Sub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(X)))) ||
4900 (NeedNSW && match(Y, m_NSWSub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(X)))))
4901 return true;
4902
4903 // X = sub (A, B), Y = sub (B, A) || X = sub nsw (A, B), Y = sub nsw (B, A)
4904 Value *A, *B;
4905 return (!NeedNSW && (match(X, m_Sub(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
4906 match(Y, m_Sub(m_Specific(B), m_Specific(A))))) ||
4907 (NeedNSW && (match(X, m_NSWSub(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
4908 match(Y, m_NSWSub(m_Specific(B), m_Specific(A)))));
4909}
4910
4911static SelectPatternResult matchSelectPattern(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
4912 FastMathFlags FMF,
4913 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
4914 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
4915 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
4916 unsigned Depth) {
4917 if (CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Pred)) {
4918 // IEEE-754 ignores the sign of 0.0 in comparisons. So if the select has one
4919 // 0.0 operand, set the compare's 0.0 operands to that same value for the
4920 // purpose of identifying min/max. Disregard vector constants with undefined
4921 // elements because those can not be back-propagated for analysis.
4922 Value *OutputZeroVal = nullptr;
4923 if (match(TrueVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) && !match(FalseVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) &&
4924 !cast<Constant>(TrueVal)->containsUndefElement())
4925 OutputZeroVal = TrueVal;
4926 else if (match(FalseVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) && !match(TrueVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) &&
4927 !cast<Constant>(FalseVal)->containsUndefElement())
4928 OutputZeroVal = FalseVal;
4929
4930 if (OutputZeroVal) {
4931 if (match(CmpLHS, m_AnyZeroFP()))
4932 CmpLHS = OutputZeroVal;
4933 if (match(CmpRHS, m_AnyZeroFP()))
4934 CmpRHS = OutputZeroVal;
4935 }
4936 }
4937
4938 LHS = CmpLHS;
4939 RHS = CmpRHS;
4940
4941 // Signed zero may return inconsistent results between implementations.
4942 // (0.0 <= -0.0) ? 0.0 : -0.0 // Returns 0.0
4943 // minNum(0.0, -0.0) // May return -0.0 or 0.0 (IEEE 754-2008 5.3.1)
4944 // Therefore, we behave conservatively and only proceed if at least one of the
4945 // operands is known to not be zero or if we don't care about signed zero.
4946 switch (Pred) {
4947 default: break;
4948 // FIXME: Include OGT/OLT/UGT/ULT.
4949 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE: case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
4950 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE: case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
4951 if (!FMF.noSignedZeros() && !isKnownNonZero(CmpLHS) &&
4952 !isKnownNonZero(CmpRHS))
4953 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4954 }
4955
4956 SelectPatternNaNBehavior NaNBehavior = SPNB_NA;
4957 bool Ordered = false;
4958
4959 // When given one NaN and one non-NaN input:
4960 // - maxnum/minnum (C99 fmaxf()/fminf()) return the non-NaN input.
4961 // - A simple C99 (a < b ? a : b) construction will return 'b' (as the
4962 // ordered comparison fails), which could be NaN or non-NaN.
4963 // so here we discover exactly what NaN behavior is required/accepted.
4964 if (CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Pred)) {
4965 bool LHSSafe = isKnownNonNaN(CmpLHS, FMF);
4966 bool RHSSafe = isKnownNonNaN(CmpRHS, FMF);
4967
4968 if (LHSSafe && RHSSafe) {
4969 // Both operands are known non-NaN.
4970 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_ANY;
4971 } else if (CmpInst::isOrdered(Pred)) {
4972 // An ordered comparison will return false when given a NaN, so it
4973 // returns the RHS.
4974 Ordered = true;
4975 if (LHSSafe)
4976 // LHS is non-NaN, so if RHS is NaN then NaN will be returned.
4977 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
4978 else if (RHSSafe)
4979 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
4980 else
4981 // Completely unsafe.
4982 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4983 } else {
4984 Ordered = false;
4985 // An unordered comparison will return true when given a NaN, so it
4986 // returns the LHS.
4987 if (LHSSafe)
4988 // LHS is non-NaN, so if RHS is NaN then non-NaN will be returned.
4989 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
4990 else if (RHSSafe)
4991 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
4992 else
4993 // Completely unsafe.
4994 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
4995 }
4996 }
4997
4998 if (TrueVal == CmpRHS && FalseVal == CmpLHS) {
4999 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
5000 Pred = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
5001 if (NaNBehavior == SPNB_RETURNS_NAN)
5002 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
5003 else if (NaNBehavior == SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER)
5004 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
5005 Ordered = !Ordered;
5006 }
5007
5008 // ([if]cmp X, Y) ? X : Y
5009 if (TrueVal == CmpLHS && FalseVal == CmpRHS) {
5010 switch (Pred) {
5011 default: return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false}; // Equality.
5012 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
5013 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5014 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
5015 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
5016 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
5017 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5018 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
5019 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
5020 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
5021 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
5022 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
5023 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE: return {SPF_FMAXNUM, NaNBehavior, Ordered};
5024 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
5025 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
5026 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
5027 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE: return {SPF_FMINNUM, NaNBehavior, Ordered};
5028 }
5029 }
5030
5031 if (isKnownNegation(TrueVal, FalseVal)) {
5032 // Sign-extending LHS does not change its sign, so TrueVal/FalseVal can
5033 // match against either LHS or sext(LHS).
5034 auto MaybeSExtCmpLHS =
5035 m_CombineOr(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_SExt(m_Specific(CmpLHS)));
5036 auto ZeroOrAllOnes = m_CombineOr(m_ZeroInt(), m_AllOnes());
5037 auto ZeroOrOne = m_CombineOr(m_ZeroInt(), m_One());
5038 if (match(TrueVal, MaybeSExtCmpLHS)) {
5039 // Set the return values. If the compare uses the negated value (-X >s 0),
5040 // swap the return values because the negated value is always 'RHS'.
5041 LHS = TrueVal;
5042 RHS = FalseVal;
5043 if (match(CmpLHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(FalseVal))))
5044 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
5045
5046 // (X >s 0) ? X : -X or (X >s -1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
5047 // (-X >s 0) ? -X : X or (-X >s -1) ? -X : X --> ABS(X)
5048 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrAllOnes))
5049 return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5050
5051 // (X >=s 0) ? X : -X or (X >=s 1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
5052 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
5053 return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5054
5055 // (X <s 0) ? X : -X or (X <s 1) ? X : -X --> NABS(X)
5056 // (-X <s 0) ? -X : X or (-X <s 1) ? -X : X --> NABS(X)
5057 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
5058 return {SPF_NABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5059 }
5060 else if (match(FalseVal, MaybeSExtCmpLHS)) {
5061 // Set the return values. If the compare uses the negated value (-X >s 0),
5062 // swap the return values because the negated value is always 'RHS'.
5063 LHS = FalseVal;
5064 RHS = TrueVal;
5065 if (match(CmpLHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(TrueVal))))
5066 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
5067
5068 // (X >s 0) ? -X : X or (X >s -1) ? -X : X --> NABS(X)
5069 // (-X >s 0) ? X : -X or (-X >s -1) ? X : -X --> NABS(X)
5070 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrAllOnes))
5071 return {SPF_NABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5072
5073 // (X <s 0) ? -X : X or (X <s 1) ? -X : X --> ABS(X)
5074 // (-X <s 0) ? X : -X or (-X <s 1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
5075 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
5076 return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
5077 }
5078 }
5079
5080 if (CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred))
5081 return matchMinMax(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS, Depth);
5082
5083 // According to (IEEE 754-2008 5.3.1), minNum(0.0, -0.0) and similar
5084 // may return either -0.0 or 0.0, so fcmp/select pair has stricter
5085 // semantics than minNum. Be conservative in such case.
5086 if (NaNBehavior != SPNB_RETURNS_ANY ||
5087 (!FMF.noSignedZeros() && !isKnownNonZero(CmpLHS) &&
5088 !isKnownNonZero(CmpRHS)))
5089 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5090
5091 return matchFastFloatClamp(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS);
5092}
5093
5094/// Helps to match a select pattern in case of a type mismatch.
5095///
5096/// The function processes the case when type of true and false values of a
5097/// select instruction differs from type of the cmp instruction operands because
5098/// of a cast instruction. The function checks if it is legal to move the cast
5099/// operation after "select". If yes, it returns the new second value of
5100/// "select" (with the assumption that cast is moved):
5101/// 1. As operand of cast instruction when both values of "select" are same cast
5102/// instructions.
5103/// 2. As restored constant (by applying reverse cast operation) when the first
5104/// value of the "select" is a cast operation and the second value is a
5105/// constant.
5106/// NOTE: We return only the new second value because the first value could be
5107/// accessed as operand of cast instruction.
5108static Value *lookThroughCast(CmpInst *CmpI, Value *V1, Value *V2,
5109 Instruction::CastOps *CastOp) {
5110 auto *Cast1 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(V1);
5111 if (!Cast1)
5112 return nullptr;
5113
5114 *CastOp = Cast1->getOpcode();
5115 Type *SrcTy = Cast1->getSrcTy();
5116 if (auto *Cast2 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(V2)) {
5117 // If V1 and V2 are both the same cast from the same type, look through V1.
5118 if (*CastOp == Cast2->getOpcode() && SrcTy == Cast2->getSrcTy())
5119 return Cast2->getOperand(0);
5120 return nullptr;
5121 }
5122
5123 auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V2);
5124 if (!C)
5125 return nullptr;
5126
5127 Constant *CastedTo = nullptr;
5128 switch (*CastOp) {
5129 case Instruction::ZExt:
5130 if (CmpI->isUnsigned())
5131 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SrcTy);
5132 break;
5133 case Instruction::SExt:
5134 if (CmpI->isSigned())
5135 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SrcTy, true);
5136 break;
5137 case Instruction::Trunc:
5138 Constant *CmpConst;
5139 if (match(CmpI->getOperand(1), m_Constant(CmpConst)) &&
5140 CmpConst->getType() == SrcTy) {
5141 // Here we have the following case:
5142 //
5143 // %cond = cmp iN %x, CmpConst
5144 // %tr = trunc iN %x to iK
5145 // %narrowsel = select i1 %cond, iK %t, iK C
5146 //
5147 // We can always move trunc after select operation:
5148 //
5149 // %cond = cmp iN %x, CmpConst
5150 // %widesel = select i1 %cond, iN %x, iN CmpConst
5151 // %tr = trunc iN %widesel to iK
5152 //
5153 // Note that C could be extended in any way because we don't care about
5154 // upper bits after truncation. It can't be abs pattern, because it would
5155 // look like:
5156 //
5157 // select i1 %cond, x, -x.
5158 //
5159 // So only min/max pattern could be matched. Such match requires widened C
5160 // == CmpConst. That is why set widened C = CmpConst, condition trunc
5161 // CmpConst == C is checked below.
5162 CastedTo = CmpConst;
5163 } else {
5164 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(C, SrcTy, CmpI->isSigned());
5165 }
5166 break;
5167 case Instruction::FPTrunc:
5168 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPExtend(C, SrcTy, true);
5169 break;
5170 case Instruction::FPExt:
5171 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPTrunc(C, SrcTy, true);
5172 break;
5173 case Instruction::FPToUI:
5174 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getUIToFP(C, SrcTy, true);
5175 break;
5176 case Instruction::FPToSI:
5177 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getSIToFP(C, SrcTy, true);
5178 break;
5179 case Instruction::UIToFP:
5180 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPToUI(C, SrcTy, true);
5181 break;
5182 case Instruction::SIToFP:
5183 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getFPToSI(C, SrcTy, true);
5184 break;
5185 default:
5186 break;
5187 }
5188
5189 if (!CastedTo)
5190 return nullptr;
5191
5192 // Make sure the cast doesn't lose any information.
5193 Constant *CastedBack =
5194 ConstantExpr::getCast(*CastOp, CastedTo, C->getType(), true);
5195 if (CastedBack != C)
5196 return nullptr;
5197
5198 return CastedTo;
5199}
5200
5201SelectPatternResult llvm::matchSelectPattern(Value *V, Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
5202 Instruction::CastOps *CastOp,
5203 unsigned Depth) {
5204 if (Depth >= MaxDepth)
5205 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5206
5207 SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V);
5208 if (!SI) return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5209
5210 CmpInst *CmpI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(SI->getCondition());
5211 if (!CmpI) return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5212
5213 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = CmpI->getPredicate();
5214 Value *CmpLHS = CmpI->getOperand(0);
5215 Value *CmpRHS = CmpI->getOperand(1);
5216 Value *TrueVal = SI->getTrueValue();
5217 Value *FalseVal = SI->getFalseValue();
5218 FastMathFlags FMF;
5219 if (isa<FPMathOperator>(CmpI))
5220 FMF = CmpI->getFastMathFlags();
5221
5222 // Bail out early.
5223 if (CmpI->isEquality())
5224 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
5225
5226 // Deal with type mismatches.
5227 if (CastOp && CmpLHS->getType() != TrueVal->getType()) {
5228 if (Value *C = lookThroughCast(CmpI, TrueVal, FalseVal, CastOp)) {
5229 // If this is a potential fmin/fmax with a cast to integer, then ignore
5230 // -0.0 because there is no corresponding integer value.
5231 if (*CastOp == Instruction::FPToSI || *CastOp == Instruction::FPToUI)
5232 FMF.setNoSignedZeros();
5233 return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS,
5234 cast<CastInst>(TrueVal)->getOperand(0), C,
5235 LHS, RHS, Depth);
5236 }
5237 if (Value *C = lookThroughCast(CmpI, FalseVal, TrueVal, CastOp)) {
5238 // If this is a potential fmin/fmax with a cast to integer, then ignore
5239 // -0.0 because there is no corresponding integer value.
5240 if (*CastOp == Instruction::FPToSI || *CastOp == Instruction::FPToUI)
5241 FMF.setNoSignedZeros();
5242 return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS,
5243 C, cast<CastInst>(FalseVal)->getOperand(0),
5244 LHS, RHS, Depth);
5245 }
5246 }
5247 return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal,
5248 LHS, RHS, Depth);
5249}
5250
5251CmpInst::Predicate llvm::getMinMaxPred(SelectPatternFlavor SPF, bool Ordered) {
5252 if (SPF == SPF_SMIN) return ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT;
5253 if (SPF == SPF_UMIN) return ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
5254 if (SPF == SPF_SMAX) return ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT;
5255 if (SPF == SPF_UMAX) return ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
5256 if (SPF == SPF_FMINNUM)
5257 return Ordered ? FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT : FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT;
5258 if (SPF == SPF_FMAXNUM)
5259 return Ordered ? FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT : FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT;
5260 llvm_unreachable("unhandled!");
5261}
5262
5263SelectPatternFlavor llvm::getInverseMinMaxFlavor(SelectPatternFlavor SPF) {
5264 if (SPF == SPF_SMIN) return SPF_SMAX;
5265 if (SPF == SPF_UMIN) return SPF_UMAX;
5266 if (SPF == SPF_SMAX) return SPF_SMIN;
5267 if (SPF == SPF_UMAX) return SPF_UMIN;
5268 llvm_unreachable("unhandled!");
5269}
5270
5271CmpInst::Predicate llvm::getInverseMinMaxPred(SelectPatternFlavor SPF) {
5272 return getMinMaxPred(getInverseMinMaxFlavor(SPF));
5273}

5275/// Return true if "icmp Pred LHS RHS" is always true.
5276static bool isTruePredicate(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, const Value *LHS,
5277 const Value *RHS, const DataLayout &DL,
5278 unsigned Depth) {
5279 assert(!LHS->getType()->isVectorTy() && "TODO: extend to handle vectors!");
5280 if (ICmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred) && LHS == RHS)
5281 return true;
5282
5283 switch (Pred) {
5284 default:
5285 return false;
5286
5287 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE: {
5288 const APInt *C;
5289
5290 // LHS s<= LHS +_{nsw} C if C >= 0
5291 if (match(RHS, m_NSWAdd(m_Specific(LHS), m_APInt(C))))
5292 return !C->isNegative();
5293 return false;
5294 }
5295
5296 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE: {
5297 const APInt *C;
5298
5299 // LHS u<= LHS +_{nuw} C for any C
5300 if (match(RHS, m_NUWAdd(m_Specific(LHS), m_APInt(C))))
5301 return true;
5302
5303 // Match A to (X +_{nuw} CA) and B to (X +_{nuw} CB)
5304 auto MatchNUWAddsToSameValue = [&](const Value *A, const Value *B,
5305 const Value *&X,
5306 const APInt *&CA, const APInt *&CB) {
5307 if (match(A, m_NUWAdd(m_Value(X), m_APInt(CA))) &&
5308 match(B, m_NUWAdd(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(CB))))
5309 return true;
5310
5311 // If X & C == 0 then (X | C) == X +_{nuw} C
5312 if (match(A, m_Or(m_Value(X), m_APInt(CA))) &&
5313 match(B, m_Or(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(CB)))) {
5314 KnownBits Known(CA->getBitWidth());
5315 computeKnownBits(X, Known, DL, Depth + 1, /*AC*/ nullptr,
5316 /*CxtI*/ nullptr, /*DT*/ nullptr);
5317 if (CA->isSubsetOf(Known.Zero) && CB->isSubsetOf(Known.Zero))
5318 return true;
5319 }
5320
5321 return false;
5322 };
5323
5324 const Value *X;
5325 const APInt *CLHS, *CRHS;
5326 if (MatchNUWAddsToSameValue(LHS, RHS, X, CLHS, CRHS))
5327 return CLHS->ule(*CRHS);
5328
5329 return false;
5330 }
5331 }
5332}
5333
5334/// Return true if "icmp Pred BLHS BRHS" is true whenever "icmp Pred
5335/// ALHS ARHS" is true. Otherwise, return None.
5336static Optional<bool>
5337isImpliedCondOperands(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, const Value *ALHS,
5338 const Value *ARHS, const Value *BLHS, const Value *BRHS,
5339 const DataLayout &DL, unsigned Depth) {
5340 switch (Pred) {
5341 default:
5342 return None;
5343
5344 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
5345 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
5346 if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, BLHS, ALHS, DL, Depth) &&
5347 isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, ARHS, BRHS, DL, Depth))
5348 return true;
5349 return None;
5350
5351 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
5352 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
5353 if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, BLHS, ALHS, DL, Depth) &&
5354 isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, ARHS, BRHS, DL, Depth))
5355 return true;
5356 return None;
5357 }
5358}
5359
5360/// Return true if the operands of the two compares match. IsSwappedOps is true
5361/// when the operands match, but are swapped.
5362static bool isMatchingOps(const Value *ALHS, const Value *ARHS,
5363 const Value *BLHS, const Value *BRHS,
5364 bool &IsSwappedOps) {
5365
5366 bool IsMatchingOps = (ALHS == BLHS && ARHS == BRHS);
5367 IsSwappedOps = (ALHS == BRHS && ARHS == BLHS);
5368 return IsMatchingOps || IsSwappedOps;
5369}
5370
5371/// Return true if "icmp1 APred X, Y" implies "icmp2 BPred X, Y" is true.
5372/// Return false if "icmp1 APred X, Y" implies "icmp2 BPred X, Y" is false.
5373/// Otherwise, return None if we can't infer anything.
5374static Optional<bool> isImpliedCondMatchingOperands(CmpInst::Predicate APred,
5375 CmpInst::Predicate BPred,
5376 bool AreSwappedOps) {
5377 // Canonicalize the predicate as if the operands were not commuted.
5378 if (AreSwappedOps)
5379 BPred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(BPred);
5380
5381 if (CmpInst::isImpliedTrueByMatchingCmp(APred, BPred))
5382 return true;
5383 if (CmpInst::isImpliedFalseByMatchingCmp(APred, BPred))
5384 return false;
5385
5386 return None;
5387}
5388
5389/// Return true if "icmp APred X, C1" implies "icmp BPred X, C2" is true.
5390/// Return false if "icmp APred X, C1" implies "icmp BPred X, C2" is false.
5391/// Otherwise, return None if we can't infer anything.
5392static Optional<bool>
5393isImpliedCondMatchingImmOperands(CmpInst::Predicate APred,
5394 const ConstantInt *C1,
5395 CmpInst::Predicate BPred,
5396 const ConstantInt *C2) {
5397 ConstantRange DomCR =
5398 ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(APred, C1->getValue());
5399 ConstantRange CR =
5400 ConstantRange::makeAllowedICmpRegion(BPred, C2->getValue());
5401 ConstantRange Intersection = DomCR.intersectWith(CR);
5402 ConstantRange Difference = DomCR.difference(CR);
5403 if (Intersection.isEmptySet())
5404 return false;
5405 if (Difference.isEmptySet())
5406 return true;
5407 return None;
5408}

5410/// Return true if LHS implies RHS is true. Return false if LHS implies RHS is
5411/// false. Otherwise, return None if we can't infer anything.
5412static Optional<bool> isImpliedCondICmps(const ICmpInst *LHS,
5413 const ICmpInst *RHS,
5414 const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue,
5415 unsigned Depth) {
5416 Value *ALHS = LHS->getOperand(0);
5417 Value *ARHS = LHS->getOperand(1);
5418 // The rest of the logic assumes the LHS condition is true. If that's not the
5419 // case, invert the predicate to make it so.
5420 ICmpInst::Predicate APred =
5421 LHSIsTrue ? LHS->getPredicate() : LHS->getInversePredicate();
5422
5423 Value *BLHS = RHS->getOperand(0);
5424 Value *BRHS = RHS->getOperand(1);
5425 ICmpInst::Predicate BPred = RHS->getPredicate();
5426
5427 // Can we infer anything when the two compares have matching operands?
5428 bool AreSwappedOps;
5429 if (isMatchingOps(ALHS, ARHS, BLHS, BRHS, AreSwappedOps)) {
5430 if (Optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondMatchingOperands(
5431 APred, BPred, AreSwappedOps))
5432 return Implication;
5433 // No amount of additional analysis will infer the second condition, so
5434 // early exit.
5435 return None;
5436 }
5437
5438 // Can we infer anything when the LHS operands match and the RHS operands are
5439 // constants (not necessarily matching)?
5440 if (ALHS == BLHS && isa<ConstantInt>(ARHS) && isa<ConstantInt>(BRHS)) {
5441 if (Optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondMatchingImmOperands(
5442 APred, cast<ConstantInt>(ARHS), BPred, cast<ConstantInt>(BRHS)))
5443 return Implication;
5444 // No amount of additional analysis will infer the second condition, so
5445 // early exit.
5446 return None;
5447 }
5448
5449 if (APred == BPred)
5450 return isImpliedCondOperands(APred, ALHS, ARHS, BLHS, BRHS, DL, Depth);
5451 return None;
5452}
5453
5454/// Return true if LHS implies RHS is true. Return false if LHS implies RHS is
5455/// false. Otherwise, return None if we can't infer anything. We expect the
5456/// RHS to be an icmp and the LHS to be an 'and' or an 'or' instruction.
5457static Optional<bool> isImpliedCondAndOr(const BinaryOperator *LHS,
5458 const ICmpInst *RHS,
5459 const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue,
5460 unsigned Depth) {
5461 // The LHS must be an 'or' or an 'and' instruction.
5462 assert((LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::And ||
5463 LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or) &&
5464 "Expected LHS to be 'and' or 'or'.");
5465
5466 assert(Depth <= MaxDepth && "Hit recursion limit");
5467
5468 // If the result of an 'or' is false, then we know both legs of the 'or' are
5469 // false. Similarly, if the result of an 'and' is true, then we know both
5470 // legs of the 'and' are true.
5471 Value *ALHS, *ARHS;
5472 if ((!LHSIsTrue && match(LHS, m_Or(m_Value(ALHS), m_Value(ARHS)))) ||
5473 (LHSIsTrue && match(LHS, m_And(m_Value(ALHS), m_Value(ARHS))))) {
5474 // FIXME: Make this non-recursion.
5475 if (Optional<bool> Implication =
5476 isImpliedCondition(ALHS, RHS, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
5477 return Implication;
5478 if (Optional<bool> Implication =
5479 isImpliedCondition(ARHS, RHS, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
5480 return Implication;
5481 return None;
5482 }
5483 return None;
5484}
5485
5486Optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedCondition(const Value *LHS, const Value *RHS,
5487 const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue,
5488 unsigned Depth) {
5489 // Bail out when we hit the limit.
5490 if (Depth == MaxDepth)
5491 return None;
5492
5493 // A mismatch occurs when we compare a scalar cmp to a vector cmp, for
5494 // example.
5495 if (LHS->getType() != RHS->getType())
5496 return None;
5497
5498 Type *OpTy = LHS->getType();
5499 assert(OpTy->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) && "Expected integer type only!");
5500
5501 // LHS ==> RHS by definition
5502 if (LHS == RHS)
5503 return LHSIsTrue;
5504
5505 // FIXME: Extending the code below to handle vectors.
5506 if (OpTy->isVectorTy())
5507 return None;
5508
5509 assert(OpTy->isIntegerTy(1) && "implied by above");
5510
5511 // Both LHS and RHS are icmps.
5512 const ICmpInst *LHSCmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(LHS);
5513 const ICmpInst *RHSCmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(RHS);
5514 if (LHSCmp && RHSCmp)
5515 return isImpliedCondICmps(LHSCmp, RHSCmp, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth);
5516
5517 // The LHS should be an 'or' or an 'and' instruction. We expect the RHS to be
5518 // an icmp. FIXME: Add support for and/or on the RHS.
5519 const BinaryOperator *LHSBO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(LHS);
5520 if (LHSBO && RHSCmp) {
5521 if ((LHSBO->getOpcode() == Instruction::And ||
5522 LHSBO->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or))
5523 return isImpliedCondAndOr(LHSBO, RHSCmp, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth);
5524 }
5525 return None;
5526}
5527
5528Optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedByDomCondition(const Value *Cond,
5529 const Instruction *ContextI,
5530 const DataLayout &DL) {
5531 assert(Cond->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) && "Condition must be bool");
5532 if (!ContextI || !ContextI->getParent())
5533 return None;
5534
5535 // TODO: This is a poor/cheap way to determine dominance. Should we use a
5536 // dominator tree (eg, from a SimplifyQuery) instead?
5537 const BasicBlock *ContextBB = ContextI->getParent();
5538 const BasicBlock *PredBB = ContextBB->getSinglePredecessor();
5539 if (!PredBB)
5540 return None;
5541
5542 // We need a conditional branch in the predecessor.
5543 Value *PredCond;
5544 BasicBlock *TrueBB, *FalseBB;
5545 if (!match(PredBB->getTerminator(), m_Br(m_Value(PredCond), TrueBB, FalseBB)))
5546 return None;
5547
5548 // The branch should get simplified. Don't bother simplifying this condition.
5549 if (TrueBB == FalseBB)
5550 return None;
5551
5552 assert((TrueBB == ContextBB || FalseBB == ContextBB) &&
5553 "Predecessor block does not point to successor?");
5554
5555 // Is this condition implied by the predecessor condition?
5556 bool CondIsTrue = TrueBB == ContextBB;
5557 return isImpliedCondition(PredCond, Cond, DL, CondIsTrue);
5558}
5559
5560static void setLimitsForBinOp(const BinaryOperator &BO, APInt &Lower,
5561 APInt &Upper, const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
5562 unsigned Width = Lower.getBitWidth();
5563 const APInt *C;
5564 switch (BO.getOpcode()) {
5565 case Instruction::Add:
5566 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && !C->isNullValue()) {
5567 // FIXME: If we have both nuw and nsw, we should reduce the range further.
5568 if (IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(&BO))) {
5569 // 'add nuw x, C' produces [C, UINT_MAX].
5570 Lower = *C;
5571 } else if (IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(&BO))) {
5572 if (C->isNegative()) {
5573 // 'add nsw x, -C' produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX - C].
5574 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
5575 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + *C + 1;
5576 } else {
5577 // 'add nsw x, +C' produces [SINT_MIN + C, SINT_MAX].
5578 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + *C;
5579 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
5580 }
5581 }
5582 }
5583 break;
5584
5585 case Instruction::And:
5586 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
5587 // 'and x, C' produces [0, C].
5588 Upper = *C + 1;
5589 break;
5590
5591 case Instruction::Or:
5592 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
5593 // 'or x, C' produces [C, UINT_MAX].
5594 Lower = *C;
5595 break;
5596
5597 case Instruction::AShr:
5598 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && C->ult(Width)) {
5599 // 'ashr x, C' produces [INT_MIN >> C, INT_MAX >> C].
5600 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width).ashr(*C);
5601 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width).ashr(*C) + 1;
5602 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
5603 unsigned ShiftAmount = Width - 1;
5604 if (!C->isNullValue() && IIQ.isExact(&BO))
5605 ShiftAmount = C->countTrailingZeros();
5606 if (C->isNegative()) {
5607 // 'ashr C, x' produces [C, C >> (Width-1)]
5608 Lower = *C;
5609 Upper = C->ashr(ShiftAmount) + 1;
5610 } else {
5611 // 'ashr C, x' produces [C >> (Width-1), C]
5612 Lower = C->ashr(ShiftAmount);
5613 Upper = *C + 1;
5614 }
5615 }
5616 break;
5617
5618 case Instruction::LShr:
5619 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && C->ult(Width)) {
5620 // 'lshr x, C' produces [0, UINT_MAX >> C].
5621 Upper = APInt::getAllOnesValue(Width).lshr(*C) + 1;
5622 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
5623 // 'lshr C, x' produces [C >> (Width-1), C].
5624 unsigned ShiftAmount = Width - 1;
5625 if (!C->isNullValue() && IIQ.isExact(&BO))
5626 ShiftAmount = C->countTrailingZeros();
5627 Lower = C->lshr(ShiftAmount);
5628 Upper = *C + 1;
5629 }
5630 break;
5631
5632 case Instruction::Shl:
5633 if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
5634 if (IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(&BO)) {
5635 // 'shl nuw C, x' produces [C, C << CLZ(C)]
5636 Lower = *C;
5637 Upper = Lower.shl(Lower.countLeadingZeros()) + 1;
5638 } else if (BO.hasNoSignedWrap()) { // TODO: What if both nuw+nsw?
5639 if (C->isNegative()) {
5640 // 'shl nsw C, x' produces [C << CLO(C)-1, C]
5641 unsigned ShiftAmount = C->countLeadingOnes() - 1;
5642 Lower = C->shl(ShiftAmount);
5643 Upper = *C + 1;
5644 } else {
5645 // 'shl nsw C, x' produces [C, C << CLZ(C)-1]
5646 unsigned ShiftAmount = C->countLeadingZeros() - 1;
5647 Lower = *C;
5648 Upper = C->shl(ShiftAmount) + 1;
5649 }
5650 }
5651 }
5652 break;
5653
5654 case Instruction::SDiv:
5655 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
5656 APInt IntMin = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
5657 APInt IntMax = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width);
5658 if (C->isAllOnesValue()) {
5659 // 'sdiv x, -1' produces [INT_MIN + 1, INT_MAX]
5660 // where C != -1 and C != 0 and C != 1
5661 Lower = IntMin + 1;
5662 Upper = IntMax + 1;
5663 } else if (C->countLeadingZeros() < Width - 1) {
5664 // 'sdiv x, C' produces [INT_MIN / C, INT_MAX / C]
5665 // where C != -1 and C != 0 and C != 1
5666 Lower = IntMin.sdiv(*C);
5667 Upper = IntMax.sdiv(*C);
5668 if (Lower.sgt(Upper))
5669 std::swap(Lower, Upper);
5670 Upper = Upper + 1;
5671 assert(Upper != Lower && "Upper part of range has wrapped!");
5672 }
5673 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
5674 if (C->isMinSignedValue()) {
5675 // 'sdiv INT_MIN, x' produces [INT_MIN, INT_MIN / -2].
5676 Lower = *C;
5677 Upper = Lower.lshr(1) + 1;
5678 } else {
5679 // 'sdiv C, x' produces [-|C|, |C|].
5680 Upper = C->abs() + 1;
5681 Lower = (-Upper) + 1;
5682 }
5683 }
5684 break;
5685
5686 case Instruction::UDiv:
5687 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && !C->isNullValue()) {
5688 // 'udiv x, C' produces [0, UINT_MAX / C].
5689 Upper = APInt::getMaxValue(Width).udiv(*C) + 1;
5690 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
5691 // 'udiv C, x' produces [0, C].
5692 Upper = *C + 1;
5693 }
5694 break;
5695
5696 case Instruction::SRem:
5697 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
5698 // 'srem x, C' produces (-|C|, |C|).
5699 Upper = C->abs();
5700 Lower = (-Upper) + 1;
5701 }
5702 break;
5703
5704 case Instruction::URem:
5705 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
5706 // 'urem x, C' produces [0, C).
5707 Upper = *C;
5708 break;
5709
5710 default:
5711 break;
5712 }
5713}
5714
5715static void setLimitsForIntrinsic(const IntrinsicInst &II, APInt &Lower,
5716 APInt &Upper) {
5717 unsigned Width = Lower.getBitWidth();
5718 const APInt *C;
5719 switch (II.getIntrinsicID()) {
5720 case Intrinsic::uadd_sat:
5721 // uadd.sat(x, C) produces [C, UINT_MAX].
5722 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) ||
5723 match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
5724 Lower = *C;
5725 break;
5726 case Intrinsic::sadd_sat:
5727 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) ||
5728 match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
5729 if (C->isNegative()) {
5730 // sadd.sat(x, -C) produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX + (-C)].
5731 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
5732 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + *C + 1;
5733 } else {
5734 // sadd.sat(x, +C) produces [SINT_MIN + C, SINT_MAX].
5735 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + *C;
5736 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
5737 }
5738 }
5739 break;
5740 case Intrinsic::usub_sat:
5741 // usub.sat(C, x) produces [0, C].
5742 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)))
5743 Upper = *C + 1;
5744 // usub.sat(x, C) produces [0, UINT_MAX - C].
5745 else if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
5746 Upper = APInt::getMaxValue(Width) - *C + 1;
5747 break;
5748 case Intrinsic::ssub_sat:
5749 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
5750 if (C->isNegative()) {
5751 // ssub.sat(-C, x) produces [SINT_MIN, -SINT_MIN + (-C)].
5752 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
5753 Upper = *C - APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + 1;
5754 } else {
5755 // ssub.sat(+C, x) produces [-SINT_MAX + C, SINT_MAX].
5756 Lower = *C - APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width);
5757 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
5758 }
5759 } else if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
5760 if (C->isNegative()) {
5761 // ssub.sat(x, -C) produces [SINT_MIN - (-C), SINT_MAX]:
5762 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) - *C;
5763 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
5764 } else {
5765 // ssub.sat(x, +C) produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX - C].
5766 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
5767 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) - *C + 1;
5768 }
5769 }
5770 break;
5771 default:
5772 break;
5773 }
5774}
5775
5776static void setLimitsForSelectPattern(const SelectInst &SI, APInt &Lower,
5777 APInt &Upper) {
5778 const Value *LHS, *RHS;
5779 SelectPatternResult R = matchSelectPattern(&SI, LHS, RHS);
5780 if (R.Flavor == SPF_UNKNOWN)
5781 return;
5782
5783 unsigned BitWidth = SI.getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
5784
5785 if (R.Flavor == SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_ABS) {
5786 // If the negation part of the abs (in RHS) has the NSW flag,
5787 // then the result of abs(X) is [0..SIGNED_MAX],
5788 // otherwise it is [0..SIGNED_MIN], as -SIGNED_MIN == SIGNED_MIN.
5789 Lower = APInt::getNullValue(BitWidth);
5790 if (cast<Instruction>(RHS)->hasNoSignedWrap())
5791 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth) + 1;
5792 else
5793 Upper = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth) + 1;
5794 return;
5795 }
5796
5797 if (R.Flavor == SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_NABS) {
5798 // The result of -abs(X) is <= 0.
5799 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
5800 Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 1);
5801 return;
5802 }
5803
5804 const APInt *C;
5805 if (!match(LHS, m_APInt(C)) && !match(RHS, m_APInt(C)))
5806 return;
5807
5808 switch (R.Flavor) {
5809 case SPF_UMIN:
5810 Upper = *C + 1;
5811 break;
5812 case SPF_UMAX:
5813 Lower = *C;
5814 break;
5815 case SPF_SMIN:
5816 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
5817 Upper = *C + 1;
5818 break;
5819 case SPF_SMAX:
5820 Lower = *C;
5821 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth) + 1;
5822 break;
5823 default:
5824 break;
5825 }
5826}
5827
5828ConstantRange llvm::computeConstantRange(const Value *V, bool UseInstrInfo) {
5829 assert(V->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && "Expected integer instruction");
5830
5831 const APInt *C;
5832 if (match(V, m_APInt(C)))
5833 return ConstantRange(*C);
5834
5835 InstrInfoQuery IIQ(UseInstrInfo);
5836 unsigned BitWidth = V->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
5837 APInt Lower = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
5838 APInt Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
5839 if (auto *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(V))
5840 setLimitsForBinOp(*BO, Lower, Upper, IIQ);
5841 else if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(V))
5842 setLimitsForIntrinsic(*II, Lower, Upper);
5843 else if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V))
5844 setLimitsForSelectPattern(*SI, Lower, Upper);
5845
5846 ConstantRange CR = ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(Lower, Upper);
5847
5848 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
5849 if (auto *Range = IIQ.getMetadata(I, LLVMContext::MD_range))
5850 CR = CR.intersectWith(getConstantRangeFromMetadata(*Range));
5851
5852 return CR;
5853}
